Subject: [PATCH 1809/2508] ASoC: Intel: Skylake: Rename the DAI used for pass
 through capture

commit eea8145644e9a270131922dd1028db33425a82e8 from
https://github.com/01org/linux-apollolake-i

Change the DAI name to remove the HDMI keyword from the pin name.
This has been added for IVI specific usecases where IEC data
is available in PCM format. This pin is used to capture
PCM and Encoded data in pass through mode, obtained on I2S interface

Change-Id: I5970e4ae94b3bf0fcde1e7ab8731f6d1befe0b20
Signed-off-by: Pardha Saradhi K <pardha.saradhi.kesapragada@intel.com>
Reviewed-on: https://git-gar-1.devtools.intel.com/gerrit/7815
Reviewed-by: Babu, Ramesh <ramesh.babu@intel.com>
Tested-by: Babu, Ramesh <ramesh.babu@intel.com>
---
 sound/soc/intel/skylake/skl-pcm.c |    4 ++--
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/intel/skylake/skl-pcm.c b/sound/soc/intel/skylake/skl-pcm.c
index 011c398..d93771a 100644
--- a/sound/soc/intel/skylake/skl-pcm.c
+++ b/sound/soc/intel/skylake/skl-pcm.c
@@ -661,10 +661,10 @@ static struct snd_soc_dai_driver skl_platform_dai[] = {
 	},
 },
 {
-	.name = "HDMI Capture Pin",
+	.name = "System Pin 5",
 	.ops = &skl_pcm_dai_ops,
 	.capture = {
-		.stream_name = "HDMI PT Capture",
+		.stream_name = "PT Capture",
 		.channels_min = HDA_STEREO,
 		.channels_max = HDA_8_CH,
 		.rates = SNDRV_PCM_RATE_32000 | SNDRV_PCM_RATE_44100 |
